ENTRY            A0035   20260202   20260327   20260327       A130
SUBENT        A0035001   20260202   20260327   20260327       A130
BIB                 14         40
TITLE      Cross section of the reaction (alpha,xn) on the
           nuclei 154Gd and 160Gd in the energy interval
           E(alpha)=47-130 MeV
AUTHOR     (D.Chmielewska,Z.Sujkowski,W.J.Ockels,J.F.W.Jansen,
           M.J.A.De Voigt)
REFERENCE  (J,BAS,42,(11),132,1978) English translation of
           (J,IZV,42,2369,1978)
           (J,NKA,23,333,1978) Method, prelim. data on figs.
INSTITUTE  (3POLIBJ,2NEDKVI)
FACILITY   (ISOCY,2NEDKVI)
ANALYSIS   (CORAB)
CORRECTION  Corrections on summing-up, electronic dead time,
           angular distribution of gamma-rays, self absorption in
           the targets, internal conversion.
MONITOR    KX-rays produced in the Gd-targets were used to
           normalize the yields to the beam flux.
METHOD     (SITA,EXTB,MOMIX)
DETECTOR   (GELI) Several Ge(Li) detectors with active volume of
           35,40,45 cm3 and target-detector distance of 20,
           44,28 and 15 cm were used.
           (GE-IN) Monitor X-ray spectra were measured with an
           intrinsic germanium detector of 10 mm diameter and 5 mm
           depth and with a 'FWHM' of about 500 eV at 122 keV
           gamma energy.
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-1) The dominant contribution to the total error
           of the cross section is made by the calibration of
           the detector registration efficiency
           (ERR-2) The error of the normalization parameter
           (ERR-T) Total error
ADD-RES    (G-SPC)
           (COMP) 'Alice+HYBRID' code
STATUS     (TABLE,,D.Chmielewska+,J,BAS,42,(11),132,1978)
           Tbls 1, 2. Several values given in the publication
           were superseded or corrected by D.Chmielewska.
           (APRVD) By D.Chmielewska
HISTORY    (19790111C)
           (19800304R) Data were received from D.Chmielewska.
           (20080609A) BIB section updated
            Corrections were made according to new EXFOR rules.
           (20260202A) SD: Entry was re-compiled.
ENDBIB              40
COMMON               2          3
ERR-1      ERR-2
PER-CENT   PER-CENT
         5.        10.
ENDCOMMON            3
ENDSUBENT           47
